Cali I’ll miss you 🫶🏼

I remember the days where I wondered why am I here? What is my purpose? Now I know I was made for such a time as this. I am a mother, a wife, and a follower of our Lord Jesus Christ. My purpose right now in this moment is to raise my daughters with a firm foundation. Raise them to be the Ruth’s and Esther’s of this generation. Raise them to be Proverbs 31 women. I’m holding the future in my arms and they smile up at me every single day.

Softball Season is Officially Over 🥎🤍
You are never too far gone. Jesus is waiting. Will you open your door and let Him in?

We are all fearfully and wonderfully made. It still amazes me how God created this entire universe and still thought about creating each and every one of us. Just imagine it real quick. How is it that we are surrounded by so much beauty from sunrise to sunsets and evening skies to changing leaves and beautiful creatures and still God thought wow I don’t have one of her! I need one of her! There’s no one in this entire world that is just like you. You were created for this moment! Yes you! You are needed and wanted and so so loved 🤍 May God bless you today, tomorrow, and always 💕

Why as a Christian household we don’t celebrate Halloween or replace it with a similar activity. This is just my personal view, opinion, and conviction. 

1 Thessalonians 5:5 
2 Corinthians 6:14
1 John 1:5
Mark 12:27
John 8:12
Leciticus 19:31

As Christians we know the difference between good and bad.  Good and evil. Day and night. We know that Jesus is the Light and satan is darkness. We know about demonic spirits and witchcraft. And I get it our kids may not understand the entirety of what Halloween may stand for, but we do. It is our job to lead them and teach them why it’s wrong to celebrate it. Did you know that just by dressing up on this day it means you allow satan to own you? Not only that, but have you seen the news about people putting blades, needles and other gross things in candy?

I am not willing to risk my daughters spiritual and physical life. There are plenty of other days where she can get sweet treats and dress up and play games. As for me and my house we will serve the Lord! Again these are my thoughts and my convictions. If you don’t feel this way by all means do what you think best for your family.

We are getting so close to ending 2023 and it still amazes how different my life looks in just 1 year! I went from trying to “make it” trying to work through social media become a “boss mom” longing to have all the high-end items being told you’re doing this for your daughters future so that she can have everything you didn’t. She won’t remember this when she’s older you being at the office and working is what she needs for her future! (Of course there’s nothing wrong if that works for you) But I went from that to a now Happy SAHM that got away from all that money crazed culture and learning that time spent with my family and caring for my family is so much more fulfilling! If I learned anything in this year it’s that money can never buy you more time with your loved ones. And although my daughter is young she definitely remembers all those days where mommy was out working instead of being there for her. I am so glad I am here now 🤍 We aren’t promised tomorrow, better yet we aren’t even promised to finish this day. Spend your time doing things you love with the people you love. God is sooo good 🙏 Have a blessed week 💕

Our December so far ♥️

Christmas 2024 ♥️ 

Getsemani’s first Christmas, Jerusalen’s excitement for this season, Our First Christmas in Tennessee. There’s so much to be thankful for, but I’m extra thankful for an extra 10 little toes that I get to kiss everyday, for a five year old that never ceases to amaze me, a loving husband that works hard to provide for his family, for our home in our new state and for our new homeschool journey / community ♥️ 

I hope you all had a Merry Christmas ♥️

Traded the Gucci’s 👠 for the Booties 🥾

This year was completely different than a year ago! We really did a whole 360 in our lives! Last year I was obsessed over all things designer and high end. This year I’ve been obsessed with Jesus, my family, and our overall well being ♥️ 

We have been so blessed this year and when I sit down to think about it all I can’t help, but praise God for allowing all these amazing things to happen to our family. It was so hard leaving our families behind and moving to TN, but we have been blessed to meet so many new friends that feel like family. I was worried that moving would make me feel anxious and homesick, but God gave me this unwavering peace. I was scared to start homeschooling because I had a baby on the way, but God surrounded me with mothers who have all gone through this and who are so supportive. I was scared my husband would struggle to find a decent job, but God opened so many doors for him to find a great fit. I was worried about my delivery being difficult, but God was there with me through all the pain. He has provided time and time again. God is so good. ♥️

I pray blessings to each and everyone of you in 2024. I pray that you get to experience the love that God has for you. ♥️

The Best Chicken & Gnocchi Soup: 🍲 
▢ 4 tablespoons Butter
▢ 1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil
▢ 1 cup finely diced onion
▢ 1/2 cup finely diced celery
▢ 2 garlic cloves, minced
▢ 1/4 cup all-purpose flour
▢ 1 quart half-and-half
▢ 28 ounces chicken broth
▢ 1/2 teaspoon thyme
▢ 1/2 teaspoon dried parsley flakes
▢ 1/4 teaspoon ground nutmeg
▢ 1 cup carrots
▢ 1 cup spinach leaves coarsely chopped
▢ Shredded Chicken
▢ 16 ounces package gnocchi

• Put your butter and olive oil in a pan on medium heat
• Sauté your onion and garlic until fragrant
• Add in your carrots and celery and sautee until soft
• in a separate container make a slurry with your flour and chicken broth. 
• Add all your sautéed veggies, slurry, spinach, and shredded chicken into your chicken broth
• Add your seasonings! 
• Add your gnocchi and cook until nice and tender. 
• Now it’s ready to be served. Enjoy!
